    {
      "text": "A 14-year-old girl presents with fatigue, weight loss, and hyperpigmentation of her skin. She also reports experiencing abdominal pain and orthostatic dizziness. Laboratory tests reveal low serum cortisol levels, elevated ACTH levels, and normal aldosterone levels. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Primary adrenal insufficiency",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Secondary adrenal insufficiency",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Tertiary adrenal insufficiency",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Cushing\u2019s syndrome",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "A. Primary adrenal insufficiency",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/J6sS5livdZq2Nz3npVvF1742215350.png"
      ],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:NaN\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> insufficiency</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Secondary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> insufficiency</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Autoimmune mediated/Addison disease</li>\n<li>Infections: TB/HIV</li>\n<li>Adrenal Hemorrhage( Waterhouse- Friderichsen syndrome)</li>\n<li>CAH due to 3 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"806eb8418c16927771822855b56695\">beta</span> -HSD deficiency</li>\n<li>Anatomical destruction of the gland</li>\n<li>Surgical removal</li>\n<li>Amyloidosis, sarcoidosis, hemochromatosis</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Congenital malformations( e.g. Holoprosencephaly)</li>\n<li>Acquired insults (CNS trauma, surgery, irradiation)</li>\n<li>Pituitary tumors</li>\n<li>Sudden discontinuation of steroids after prolonged treatment</li>\n<li>Genetic defects</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
