    {
      "text": "A 16-year-old girl presents with hypertension, hypokalemia, and amenorrhea. She has a history of reduced secondary sexual characteristics and has not menstruated since puberty. Lab reports reveal elevated serum aldosterone levels, normal cortisol levels, and low serum testosterone levels. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
